#Text=United States wins Wheelchair Rugby Tri-Nations Series in Sydney
#Text=Friday , September 20 , 2013
#Text=Cathedral Square , Sydney — The United States won the Wheelchair Rugby Tri-Nations Series against Australia and New Zealand at Cathedral Square in Sydney today .
#Text=Chuck Aoki ( US ) and Ryley Batt ( Aus)Image : Jeff Crow Australian Paralympic Committee .
#Text=Wheelchair Rugby Tri-Nation series- New Zealand Wheel Blacks Image : Hawkeye7 .
#Text=Wheelchair Rugby Tri-Nation series- Australia v New Zealand Image : Hawkeye7 .
#Text=Wheelchair Rugby Tri-Nation series - night match - Australia v United States Image : Hawkeye7 .
#Text=Wheelchair Rugby Tri-Nation series- Australia v New Zealand Image : Hawkeye7 .
#Text=Game Four , played at 12:30 yesterday , was played between the New Zealand Wheel Blacks and the Australian Steelers before a lunchtime crowd .
#Text=Australia scored six straight goals in second quarter , to lead 29-44 at half time , and eventually came out the winners 41-57 .
#Text=The game featured an unusual duel between two 3.5- point players , Australia 's Ryley Batt and New Zealand 's Barney Konerferisi .
#Text=In Game Five , played under lights at 17:30 yesterday , the United States proved too good for New Zealand , winning 36-62 .
#Text=Game Six followed immediately after at 19:30 .
#Text=This game , between Australia and United States attracted a sizable and animated crowd that filled the venue .
#Text=Australia had only beaten the United States once in the last seven years .
#Text=The Steelers managed to win gold at the 2012 Summer Paralympic Games in London without having to play them .
#Text=Australia opened the game with three straight goals , but the United States caught up , and the score was 14-15 at quarter time , after a last second United States score was counted .
#Text=While the United States frequently rotated its players , the Steelers had Ryley Batt , Chris Bond , Ryan Scott and Nazim Erdem on the court the whole time .
#Text=Their strong defence caused timeouts and subsequent turnovers .
#Text=Low-pointer Ryan Scott became an unlikely hero by prompting two turnovers .
#Text=Australia won 64-53 .
#Text=Game Seven was the Semi-Final , between Australia and New Zealand , and was played at 12:00 today .
#Text=The weather was warm and sunny .
#Text=The New Zealanders performed a Haka , but it did not bring victory .
#Text=This time Australia rotated its players , and Bond and Batt were on the court together only briefly just before half time , and again in the last four minutes .
#Text=Australia won handily , 62-45 .
#Text=The Final game was therefore between the United States and Australia under lights at 17:00 on today .
#Text=The commentators called it " Friday Night Footy " .

#Text=Australia once again played Bond , Batt , Erdem and Scott together , and took off to a three-goal lead , but the United States fought back with good defensive plays , tying the score at 14-all at quarter time .
#Text=The United States scored three goals straight in the second quarter to take a 29-25 lead at half time .
#Text=Hopes that Australia could repeat its win of the night before were dashed .
#Text=The United States team had tight discipline and made few mistakes , in the end , winning 58-54 .
#Text=Medals were presented to the players , coaches and team staff by Greg Hartung , the President of the Australian Paralympic Committee .
#Text=The players of all three teams voted for the Most Valuable Player of the series , which went to Ryley Batt .
#Text=This is believed to be the first time that an international wheelchair rugby tournament has been held outdoors .
